<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927355>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 14A−E. Latouchia maculosa spec. nov., photos taken in the field. A Habitat at the type locality. B Closed trapdoor (indicated by white arrow). C Burrow entrance with the trapdoor fully opened (note the dense white silk lining of the burrow walls and of the inside of the trapdoor). D Characteristic defence behaviour of many fossorial trapdoor spiders: clinging onto the inside of the trapdoor and pulling it back into the closed position against an external force. E Living female outside her burrow." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4927355/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927349>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 11A−L. Latouchia maculosa spec. nov., females (A−E paratype PS-026; F paratype PS-027; G Huay Yang, 90 m; H paratype PS-036; I Pala-U, 290 m, J−L presumably conspecific specimens from north of Prachuap Khiri Khan Province, not listed). A Habitus, dorsal. B–C Right tibia and patella III (B prolateral, C retrolateral). D Spinnerets, ventral. E−L Variation in the monopartite spermathecae of eight different specimens (note long, conical, racemose structures). Abbreviations: ds—demisaddle, ms—macro-spigots on distal and medial article of PLS." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4927349/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927353>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 13A–D. Latouchia maculosa spec. nov., males, variation in the habitus of four ethanol-preserved paratypes. Scale line: 10 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4927353/files/figure.png" .

